From 0b2185d3c250920fee47863fad54d04e6b66873c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: robobun <robobun@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 30 Apr 2026 20:25:11 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Implement import defer (TC39 Stage 3)

Adds runtime semantics for the deferred module evaluation proposal
(https://tc39.es/proposal-defer-import-eval/) on top of the existing
parser support for 'import defer * as ns from ...'.

AbstractModuleRecord:
- ModulePhase enum (Evaluation / Defer), carried on ModuleRequest and
  ImportEntry.
- Separate m_moduleDeferredNamespaceObject cache; getModuleNamespace()
  takes a phase and returns the appropriate object.
- gatherAsynchronousTransitiveDependencies(): post-order DFS that
  collects unexecuted TLA modules in a deferred subgraph.
- innerModuleEvaluation() builds an evaluationList per the proposed
  algorithm: defer-phase requests contribute only their async
  transitive deps; evaluation-phase requests are recursed as before.
  No overhead when the module has no deferred imports.

CyclicModuleRecord:
- readyForSyncExecution(): iterative DFS that mirrors the spec's
  ReadyForSyncExecution(module, seen).
- initializeEnvironment() passes ImportEntry.phase to
  getModuleNamespace() so 'import defer * as ns' binds a deferred
  namespace.

JSModuleNamespaceObject:
- m_isDeferred flag; deferred instances get @@toStringTag =
  'Deferred Module' and hide 'then' (IsSymbolLikeNamespaceKey).
- ensureDeferredNamespaceEvaluation() implements EvaluateModuleSync:
  checks readyForSyncExecution(), calls module.Evaluate(), and throws
  the promise's rejection value synchronously.
- Hooked into getOwnPropertySlotCommon / deleteProperty /
  getOwnPropertyNames / defineOwnProperty so any string-key access
  triggers evaluation.

ModuleAnalyzer / NodesAnalyzeModule:
- Thread ImportDeclarationNode::ImportType::Deferred through to a
  defer-phase requested-module + namespace ImportEntry.
- Requested-module dedup is now per (specifier, phase).

Parser:
- Recognise 'import.defer(' alongside 'import.meta'; createImportExpr
  gains an isDeferred argument.
- ImportNode carries m_isDeferred; when set, emitBytecode passes the
  phase as a third argument to @importModule.

Runtime:
- globalFuncImportModule reads the optional phase argument; when
  Defer, chains the import promise through a new
  InternalMicrotask::ImportDeferModuleNamespace that swaps the result
  to the deferred namespace for the same module record. Lazy
  evaluation for the dynamic form (skipping Evaluate() entirely) still
  requires threading phase through ContinueDynamicImport.

Options:
- useImportDefer flipped to true.
